11
00:02:07.711 --> 00:02:08.712 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's right!

12
00:02:08.879 --> 00:02:11.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Gentlemen,
that option has already been considered.

13
00:02:18.764 --> 00:02:21.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
We have a much more
urgent concern.

14
00:02:21.183 --> 00:02:23.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>This city is built</i>
<i>on three separate levels,</i>

15
00:02:23.560 --> 00:02:25.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>with the Stern Medaille Area</i>
<i>at its center.</i>

16
00:02:26.063 --> 00:02:29.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Should the foundation collapse,</i>
<i>everything will go down with it.</i>

17
00:02:29.650 --> 00:02:31.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[mayor]
They're holding the entire city hostage.

18
00:02:32.194 --> 00:02:34.404 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We must be careful
not to do anything reckless.

19
00:02:34.571 --> 00:02:36.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[council member 1] Are you saying
we should give in to terrorists?

20
00:02:36.865 --> 00:02:39.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[council member 2] We can't do something
that irresponsible!

21
00:02:39.660 --> 00:02:41.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How could we find ourselves
in this position?

22
00:02:42.162 --> 00:02:44.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You said the heroes would handle this!
That they were on top of it!

23
00:02:49.044 --> 00:02:52.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's horrible, Ms. Agnes... Isn't there
anything we can do to help out?

24
00:02:52.464 --> 00:02:53.715 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Agnes]
<i>Sorry, not right now.</i>

25
00:02:54.132 --> 00:02:57.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So we have to sit by and
just let these bastards do as they please?

26
00:02:57.678 --> 00:03:01.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
With all our abilities...
I can't believe there's nothing we can do.

27
00:03:01.306 --> 00:03:04.017 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. I'm positive
that there's something we can do!

28
00:03:04.101 --> 00:03:06.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We just have to stand by and
wait until that time comes!

29
00:03:11.775 --> 00:03:13.610 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I understand how you feel.

30
00:03:13.985 --> 00:03:16.154 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But don't forget,
people's lives are at stake---

31
00:03:16.321 --> 00:03:17.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I happen to be aware of that!

32
00:03:17.656 --> 00:03:18.657 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasping]

33
00:03:18.824 --> 00:03:21.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come on, you guys.
This is no time to fight.

34
00:03:21.868 --> 00:03:24.371 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We need to pull together as a group
and stay focused.

35
00:03:27.958 --> 00:03:29.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's eating him today?

36
00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:37.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry, guys! I'm afraid I must've
gotten on his nerves!

37
00:03:38.051 --> 00:03:39.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What did you say to him?

38
00:03:39.428 --> 00:03:42.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, I thought I'd tell him how I got
my code name, it is kind of interesting.

39
00:03:43.056 --> 00:03:44.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

40
00:03:44.224 --> 00:03:48.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The 'Ko' in Kotetsu means 'Tiger'.
That's why I'm called Wild Tiger. Get it?

41
00:03:48.854 --> 00:03:49.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

42
00:03:50.355 --> 00:03:52.441 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Rock Bison] Why would you bring that
stuff up now?

43
00:03:52.566 --> 00:03:55.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Origami] Inappropriate!
No wonder the guy got so upset.

44
00:03:55.652 --> 00:03:58.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah. I'm gonna go
apologize to him.

45
00:04:00.365 --> 00:04:03.452 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How could he be so oblivious
to what's happening right now?

46
00:04:03.785 --> 00:04:06.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, honey.
Something else is going on there.

47
00:04:08.915 --> 00:04:10.208 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Bunny...!

48
00:04:10.542 --> 00:04:13.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wait up a minute! Where
are you going?

49
00:04:15.255 --> 00:04:17.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry 'bout that. I
kinda lost it back there.

50
00:04:18.049 --> 00:04:20.594 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know you were
only trying to help out.

51
00:04:30.313 --> 00:04:32.089 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[glass shatters]
-[Barnaby grunts]

52
00:04:35.150 --> 00:04:37.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Right when I found
the bastard!

53
00:04:37.819 --> 00:04:39.404 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Agnes]
<i>We have an emergency!</i>

54
00:04:40.155 --> 00:04:41.239 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can't make you
out--

55
00:04:41.364 --> 00:04:44.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The powered exosuits destroyed one
of the support columns in East Bronze!

56
00:04:54.169 --> 00:04:57.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sky High and Blue Rose! You have to
head to the scene immediately!

57
00:04:59.341 --> 00:05:01.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're responding.
What do you want us to focus on?

58
00:05:02.177 --> 00:05:03.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Ignore the powered exosuits.</i>

59
00:05:04.095 --> 00:05:06.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>You need to save people</i>
<i>and prevent widespread panic.</i>

60
00:05:07.224 --> 00:05:08.683 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm going with them, Agnes!

61
00:05:08.809 --> 00:05:10.727 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I'm ordering you to stay!</i>

62
00:05:11.061 --> 00:05:12.312 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Why would you do that?</i>

63
00:05:12.395 --> 00:05:15.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There could easily be another attack.
Everyone else is on standby.

64
00:05:15.774 --> 00:05:19.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We should be doing something right now!</i>
<i>What's taking so long to make a decision?</i>

65
00:05:22.072 --> 00:05:26.034 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[news anchor] <i>With Stern Bild on the</i>
<i>brink of destruction, everyone's asking,</i>

66
00:05:26.117 --> 00:05:29.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>"Why aren't the city leaders</i>
<i>and the heroes mobilizing to fight back?"</i>

67
00:05:30.205 --> 00:05:33.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Tiger's right.
We can't just wait for the next attack.

68
00:05:35.961 --> 00:05:37.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Kriem] <i>We've been waiting.</i>

69
00:05:37.546 --> 00:05:40.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Waiting for someone in charge</i>
<i>to respond to our demands.</i>

70
00:05:40.674 --> 00:05:42.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Perhaps you don't believe</i>
<i>that we're serious...</i>

71
00:05:44.553 --> 00:05:47.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Our next attack will be in</i>
<i>an hour at eleven o'clock</i>.

72
00:05:47.889 --> 00:05:50.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We'll decide on the location</i>
<i>by rolling a pair of dice.</i>

73
00:05:52.394 --> 00:05:55.105 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm not waiting 'til
then! Come on, Bunny!

74
00:05:55.897 --> 00:05:58.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Agnes] <i>Don't do this!</i>
<i>You're disobeying a direct order!</i>

75
00:05:58.984 --> 00:06:01.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[council member 1] They plan to destroy
another support column!

76
00:06:01.152 --> 00:06:03.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[council member 2] How do we know that
for sure? They could be bluffing!

77
00:06:03.579 --> 00:06:04.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[council member 1]
What are you talking about?

78
00:06:04.948 --> 00:06:06.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The city's already beginning to tilt!

79
00:06:07.742 --> 00:06:11.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We can't drag this out any longer.
We're facing a potential disaster!

80
00:06:11.788 --> 00:06:13.707 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have to make a
decision, Mr. Mayor.

81
00:06:13.832 --> 00:06:15.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Huh?
-We have no choice...

82
00:06:16.209 --> 00:06:17.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have to release Jake!

83
00:06:17.919 --> 00:06:21.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What? Wait just a minute here!
Don't put all of this on me!

84
00:06:22.132 --> 00:06:25.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll accept full responsibility, if that's
what it takes to get through this...

85
00:06:25.844 --> 00:06:28.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you're the only one
who must make the final decision.

86
00:06:28.471 --> 00:06:31.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes, right.
But if by any chance things go wrong...

87
00:06:32.392 --> 00:06:37.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, I've deployed</i>
<i>Sky High and Blue Rose, as you requested.</i>

88
00:06:37.272 --> 00:06:39.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But we have one little problem...</i>

89
00:06:40.609 --> 00:06:42.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why the hell are you
just sitting on your asses?

90
00:06:43.153 --> 00:06:45.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Isn't your top priority
to save the lives of citizens?

91
00:06:45.447 --> 00:06:47.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Mayor] What? What are you doing here?

92
00:06:48.199 --> 00:06:49.326 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighing]

93
00:06:49.576 --> 00:06:52.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Listen, let us worry about Jake
and his gang!

94
00:06:52.245 --> 00:06:54.372 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We heroes
always come through for you!

95
00:06:54.789 --> 00:06:55.874 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Usually...

96
00:06:56.583 --> 00:06:58.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then what the hell are you waiting for?

97
00:06:58.793 --> 00:07:02.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're not trying to protect
that thing of yours, are you?

98
00:07:04.007 --> 00:07:04.925 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thing?

99
00:07:05.342 --> 00:07:09.179 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can't think of the word.
Uh, self... something or other.

100
00:07:09.554 --> 00:07:11.348 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Self-interests.
-Yeah, that's it!

101
00:07:11.723 --> 00:07:12.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ahh!

102
00:07:13.141 --> 00:07:15.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's no point in
beating around the bush!

103
00:07:15.477 --> 00:07:18.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You all have friends and family in
the city. Don't you want to protect them?

104
00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:22.609 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then you need to make a
decision quickly!

105
00:07:22.817 --> 00:07:25.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And rise above your own
whachamacallits.

106
00:07:25.487 --> 00:07:27.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Self-interests.
-Thank you!

107
00:07:27.739 --> 00:07:31.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have to say, even though my friend here
wasn't very clear,

108
00:07:31.242 --> 00:07:32.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he does make a good point.

109
00:07:33.328 --> 00:07:34.204 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm.

110
00:07:34.496 --> 00:07:36.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Chuckman] Listen to the man! He's
absolutely right!

111
00:07:37.082 --> 00:07:37.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasping]

112
00:07:38.083 --> 00:07:40.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Except he's wrong about
capturing us!

113
00:07:40.585 --> 00:07:41.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasping]

114
00:07:41.670 --> 00:07:44.798 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We got tired of waiting
for an answer from you big-shots!

115
00:07:45.256 --> 00:07:47.926 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm here to work out
the details of your surrender!

116
00:07:48.051 --> 00:07:49.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're one of the Ouroboros?

117
00:07:52.222 --> 00:07:55.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You can all call me Hans Chuckman.
I'm here to negotiate!

118
00:07:55.892 --> 00:07:57.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You have some nerve,
barging into this place!

119
00:07:57.978 --> 00:08:00.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh, really? I don't suppose
the same could be said of you...

120
00:08:01.106 --> 00:08:04.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Stop it, both of you!
People's lives are at stake!

121
00:08:05.568 --> 00:08:09.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Sorry! People's lives
are the top priority! I agree

122
00:08:11.866 --> 00:08:13.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now that we've settled that, tell me.

123
00:08:14.244 --> 00:08:17.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What have you big-shots
decided to do? Huh?

124
00:08:17.831 --> 00:08:19.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh... Well, we thought...

125
00:08:19.958 --> 00:08:22.335 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In order to ensure
the safety of our people,

126
00:08:22.460 --> 00:08:24.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
we'd like you to withdraw
your powered exosuits---

127
00:08:24.462 --> 00:08:26.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ha! You've got to
be kidding me!

128
00:08:26.464 --> 00:08:28.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Apparently,
you don't understand the situation!

129
00:08:28.717 --> 00:08:31.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We were just hoping to reach
some kind of accommodation.

130
00:08:31.678 --> 00:08:33.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're not making any deals!

131
00:08:33.722 --> 00:08:36.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've been offered
one final chance to surrender.

132
00:08:36.266 --> 00:08:39.185 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Funny you should say that,
we were just talking about that.

133
00:08:39.436 --> 00:08:41.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's no use trying
to buy time.

134
00:08:41.563 --> 00:08:43.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If we don't hear from you
before the deadline,

135
00:08:44.107 --> 00:08:46.151 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the decision is simple. Kaboom!

136
00:08:52.615 --> 00:08:55.702 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Residents of Stern Bild,</i>
<i>this is an important announcement.</i>

137
00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:58.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>Your safety is our top priority,</i>

138
00:08:58.580 --> 00:09:00.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>and therefore,</i>
<i>we have concluded the following...</i>

139
00:09:00.874 --> 00:09:04.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>We are unable to defend the city,</i>
<i>and we cannot allow any more casualties.</i>

140
00:09:04.836 --> 00:09:07.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>That being said, we have decided</i>
<i>to give in to the enemy's demands,</i>

141
00:09:07.839 --> 00:09:09.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>and release Jake Martinez at once.</i>

142
00:09:10.258 --> 00:09:12.135 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Good! Should've done
that earlier!

143
00:09:27.400 --> 00:09:33.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[humming]

144
00:09:38.453 --> 00:09:41.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, Jake! I thought you were in here
for the rest of your life!

145
00:09:41.998 --> 00:09:46.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Want to know why I'm being released today?
There's a simple answer...

146
00:09:46.586 --> 00:09:50.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You see, I'm Jake...
and you, my friend, are not.

147
00:09:51.216 --> 00:09:55.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No big deal. I mean...the next time
you see me, we will still be friends.

148
00:09:55.929 --> 00:09:58.473 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wait, there won't
be a next time.

149
00:10:02.268 --> 00:10:03.937 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunting]

150
00:10:09.818 --> 00:10:13.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I kinda figured this was
your doing... Kriem...

151
00:10:14.781 --> 00:10:18.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sorry you had to be in there
for so long, Mister Jake. We were trying.

152
00:10:18.993 --> 00:10:21.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How did you finally
do it? [chuckling]

153
00:10:21.913 --> 00:10:24.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think I'll leave that
one to your imagination.

154
00:10:25.041 --> 00:10:27.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A secret, huh? I
love secrets.

155
00:10:27.961 --> 00:10:30.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And I love a
woman with secrets.

156
00:10:33.633 --> 00:10:35.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[news anchor]
<i>Jake Martinez has now been released,</i>

157
00:10:35.927 --> 00:10:38.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>and is leaving the prison in a helicopter.</i>

158
00:10:40.598 --> 00:10:43.143 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
<i>The question is, has</i>
<i>destruction been averted?</i>

159
00:10:43.476 --> 00:10:45.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I guess we're all just
gonna have to be patient.

160
00:10:46.229 --> 00:10:48.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Tiger] Once they've withdrawn
their forces and the people are safe,

161
00:10:49.023 --> 00:10:50.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
then we'll make our move.

162
00:10:50.567 --> 00:10:53.528 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's a daring plan.
I hope everything goes okay.

163
00:10:53.778 --> 00:10:56.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It will. As long as they don't know
what we've done.

164
00:11:03.163 --> 00:11:05.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This city's still a dump,
nothing's changed, I see.

165
00:11:10.753 --> 00:11:12.088 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How 'bout a toast?

166
00:11:12.881 --> 00:11:14.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Better not, I'm at the controls.

167
00:11:15.258 --> 00:11:17.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're so serious, my friend.

168
00:11:21.556 --> 00:11:24.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What do you think you're going to
accomplish by keeping me here?

169
00:11:24.851 --> 00:11:26.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The city's about to sink!

170
00:11:26.686 --> 00:11:29.856 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Origami] We're well aware of the
problem. That's where I come in.

171
00:11:30.231 --> 00:11:31.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

172
00:11:33.359 --> 00:11:34.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasping]

173
00:11:34.652 --> 00:11:36.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry you have to do this.

174
00:11:36.404 --> 00:11:39.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I'm absolutely
sure that you'll be able to pull it off.

175
00:11:40.742 --> 00:11:44.204 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Of course, if things go wrong,
your life will be in grave danger.

176
00:11:44.370 --> 00:11:48.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You can still--
-I'm fine. After all, I am still a hero.

177
00:11:49.792 --> 00:11:52.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The fact is, this is something
only I can do, right?

178
00:11:53.296 --> 00:11:54.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll do it.

179
00:11:58.760 --> 00:12:00.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[Tiger] Hey, Origami!
-Hm?

180
00:12:01.221 --> 00:12:02.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You forgot this.

181
00:12:04.015 --> 00:12:05.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you.

182
00:12:05.892 --> 00:12:10.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If something goes wrong, contact us.
We'll all be standing by to back you up.

183
00:12:10.346 --> 00:12:11.264 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Got it!

184
00:12:11.481 --> 00:12:14.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Our future now depends
upon your abilities.

185
00:12:15.026 --> 00:12:17.362 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good luck... Origami Cyclone.

186
00:12:17.612 --> 00:12:18.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks!

187
00:12:20.949 --> 00:12:24.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been meaning to ask,
what's the name of our pilot?

188
00:12:24.535 --> 00:12:25.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is Hans Chuckman.

189
00:12:26.204 --> 00:12:30.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As you probably figured out, he's not
a NEXT, but he believes in our cause.

190
00:12:30.708 --> 00:12:34.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
A regular human being?
That explains why he's so boring.

191
00:12:35.505 --> 00:12:39.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>He wants to help us create</i>
<i>a Utopian nation controlled by NEXTs.</i>

192
00:12:39.676 --> 00:12:41.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>A world ruled by you.</i>

193
00:12:41.719 --> 00:12:45.890 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Oh... I guess that means you aspire to
become a NEXT someday?

194
00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:50.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm afraid that's impossible.
Isn't that right, Kriem?

195
00:12:50.603 --> 00:12:51.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's true.

196
00:12:51.771 --> 00:12:55.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's too bad for you humans...
but NEXTs are God's chosen ones.

197
00:12:59.070 --> 00:13:00.697 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Chuckman!
-What is it, ma'am?

198
00:13:00.905 --> 00:13:03.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Since Mr. Jake has been freed
as planned,

199
00:13:03.366 --> 00:13:05.493 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
you can now prepare
to release the hostages.

200
00:13:05.743 --> 00:13:07.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Yes.
-Hold on!

201
00:13:09.205 --> 00:13:11.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Tell me about
these hostages.

202
00:13:14.252 --> 00:13:15.712 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[Maverick]
<i>Do you have any updates?</i>

203
00:13:15.920 --> 00:13:18.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No sir---There's been no
movement whatsoever.

204
00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:19.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see.

205
00:13:23.594 --> 00:13:26.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What's happening? When are they
going to pull back their forces?

206
00:13:27.140 --> 00:13:29.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Easy! Let's not panic,
gentlemen.

207
00:13:29.559 --> 00:13:32.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It's only been a half-hour
since Jake Martinez was released.

208
00:13:32.812 --> 00:13:36.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe they're in the process
of mobilizing their forces to pull out!

209
00:13:38.192 --> 00:13:40.987 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have to agree.
Our plan is right on track.

210
00:13:41.195 --> 00:13:43.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We at least need to wait until
Origami Cyclone

211
00:13:43.573 --> 00:13:45.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
has a chance to contact us.

212
00:13:45.241 --> 00:13:48.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's the key to the whole operation.
You think he's all right out there?

213
00:13:49.078 --> 00:13:52.915 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He's still alive. We're able to monitor
his vital signs through sensors.

214
00:13:53.249 --> 00:13:56.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We only have to worry
if that green tracking signal turns red.

215
00:13:58.379 --> 00:14:00.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey! What's happening?

216
00:14:00.256 --> 00:14:02.008 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We kept up our end of the bargain!

217
00:14:02.216 --> 00:14:05.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't ask me! I don't know how they think
or what they plan to do!

218
00:14:05.678 --> 00:14:08.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, calm down! We need
to trust Origami.

219
00:14:11.225 --> 00:14:15.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I am calm! Tell me what the Ouroboros
is planning! Answer me!

220
00:14:16.814 --> 00:14:19.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hey, you're going too far.
Cool it, Bunny.

221
00:14:25.615 --> 00:14:27.825 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm gonna go out and take
a break.

222
00:14:29.577 --> 00:14:30.828 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[coughing]

223
00:14:31.079 --> 00:14:35.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're not idiots. They probably
caught on to your stupid plan!

224
00:14:46.636 --> 00:14:48.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please, just leave me alone.

225
00:14:55.478 --> 00:14:57.730 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
How long do you plan on
standing out here?

226
00:14:58.523 --> 00:15:01.609 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's none of your business.
Just leave me alone.

227
00:15:03.277 --> 00:15:05.655 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know I must seem to be
acting irrationally.

228
00:15:06.739 --> 00:15:09.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You really don't seem
much different than usual.

229
00:15:09.617 --> 00:15:14.205 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When I finally see Jake face to face...
I'm not sure I'll have much self-control.

230
00:15:15.289 --> 00:15:17.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Quit worrying about it,
I've got you covered.

231
00:15:18.042 --> 00:15:20.211 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not gonna let you do anything stupid.

232
00:15:21.212 --> 00:15:25.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Relying on others for help
every now and then, not such a bad thing.

233
00:15:26.092 --> 00:15:28.177 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, Kotetsu! Barnaby!

234
00:15:29.554 --> 00:15:31.013 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We've got some trouble!

235
00:15:32.098 --> 00:15:33.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Jake] <i>Citizens of Stern Bild...</i>

236
00:15:34.475 --> 00:15:39.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Thank you for releasing me.</i>
<i>I speak to you now as a free man...</i>

237
00:15:39.480 --> 00:15:40.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's Jake!

238
00:15:40.523 --> 00:15:42.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I had no idea why I was</i>
<i>being released...</i>

239
00:15:42.942 --> 00:15:45.778 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>No one told me</i>
<i>it was negotiated in exchange for</i>

240
00:15:45.987 --> 00:15:48.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>sparing the lives</i>
<i>of useless human garbage.</i>

241
00:15:49.157 --> 00:15:51.742 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As a result...
I've made a decision...

242
00:15:52.243 --> 00:15:54.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
not to release any of
the hostages.

243
00:15:55.997 --> 00:15:57.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What? Am I hearing this right?

244
00:15:57.915 --> 00:16:00.751 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>In other words, for those of you</i>
<i>who are still confused,</i>

245
00:16:00.918 --> 00:16:03.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>your lives will remain in the</i>
<i>palm of my hand.</i>

246
00:16:03.504 --> 00:16:06.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>After all, you'll do anything I want!</i>
<i>Am I right about that?</i>

247
00:16:06.966 --> 00:16:10.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I guess we're gonna find out! Bye bye now.</i>

248
00:16:12.305 --> 00:16:13.431 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[grunting]

249
00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:17.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well...

250
00:16:17.310 --> 00:16:21.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Origami's still safe. Damn it,
how much longer is this all gonna take?

251
00:16:22.148 --> 00:16:23.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh...

252
00:16:24.400 --> 00:16:27.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What's going on here?
Mr. Maverick?

253
00:16:28.446 --> 00:16:32.867 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Actually, we expected this to happen.
Our plan is going just fine.

254
00:16:33.117 --> 00:16:35.495 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now all we have to do is
wait for our spy,

255
00:16:35.578 --> 00:16:38.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Origami Cyclone, to tell us how
the powered exosuits work.

256
00:16:38.664 --> 00:16:40.875 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then, we'll know how to
attack the enemy.

257
00:16:41.083 --> 00:16:43.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
What? How am I supposed to
explain this to the people

258
00:16:43.544 --> 00:16:44.671 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
who thought this was over?

259
00:16:46.172 --> 00:16:49.842 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is crazy! The population of this city
is going to be up in arms!

260
00:16:49.926 --> 00:16:52.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How am I supposed to--
-I have a plan to address that.

261
00:16:54.764 --> 00:16:58.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[reporters clamoring]

262
00:16:59.560 --> 00:17:01.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You'll have to hold your questions.

263
00:17:01.562 --> 00:17:04.148 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Maverick
is handling everything at the moment.

264
00:17:04.315 --> 00:17:06.859 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Mr. Maverick is?
You're the mayor, aren't you?

265
00:17:06.984 --> 00:17:10.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Of course I am! We'll hold an interview
after everything's resolved!

266
00:17:10.221 --> 00:17:11.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That'll have to
do for now.

267
00:17:11.452 --> 00:17:13.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[reporter] The people deserve a
straight answer from their mayor!

268
00:17:15.535 --> 00:17:17.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes. We're meeting with the press
at two o'clock.

269
00:17:18.079 --> 00:17:20.081 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll explain what we can
at that time.

270
00:17:20.289 --> 00:17:22.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hopefully, that will
satisfy everyone.

271
00:17:26.837 --> 00:17:28.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You wanted to see us, sir?

272
00:17:28.839 --> 00:17:31.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-[man 1] Mr. Maverick's about to speak!
-[man 2] Something's going on!

273
00:17:32.009 --> 00:17:35.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Maverick] <i>As you all know, Stern Bild</i>
<i>is undergoing a terrorist attack.</i>

274
00:17:36.055 --> 00:17:38.891 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The Mayor decided that</i>
<i>your lives took top priority,</i>

275
00:17:39.016 --> 00:17:40.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and therefore, acted accordingly.</i>

276
00:17:41.227 --> 00:17:43.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Rather than put</i>
<i>your family's safety at risk,</i>

277
